## 4. Pagination idiom

- Style: `<page | cursor | offset | link-header>`, param `<param>` (see
  `pagination` in connection.json).
- Use `http_paginate` for page-style listings (merges top-level or
  `items` arrays, max 10 pages per call); for other styles, loop
  `http_request` with `<cursor/offset field>` from the previous response.
- The envelope's `truncated: true` means the RESPONSE BODY was cut at the
  byte cap — that is not "no more pages." Narrow the request (smaller
  `per_page`, field filters) instead of paging past it.

